replies.text: I did. But if I'm being honest, the new volume 1 DVD is literal garbage. It uses artwork from the other Sonic shows rather than SU itself. I was like, what the fuck? I guess maybe they thought some people wouldn't notice? I mean, I fucking did. Maybe I noticed before you did because I'm a true fan and shit? I don't know. But what I do know is that I feel personally attacked for it because they continue to ignore this show and yet they think they can slap the old episodes into a collectiong to make a quick buck? What a waste of money. What a waste of god damn time. There are tons and tons of dvd's that already contain the entire 40 episodes, so why the fuck are they selling HALF in the dvd set? Now if it included a newly drawn cover, or an album of Tyley Ross's music as an extra, I would think about getting it for that alone, but it doesn't. With that said, the price is nice and it's still a good place to start for those look ing to get into Sonic Underground, so I can allow it to exist.
replies.author: Tamers12345

replies.text: @Tamers12345  You do have a point there. I had to look back at the box and I noticed some wrong art being used. I’m gonna go find a better box set so I can get the true, genuine Sonic Underground Experience! But yes, the price was attractive. Still no Blu-Ray tho. Even tho Sonic Underground wasn’t made in HD, they should stop being little bitches and just give us the whole set on Blu-Ray.
